@TheCauldron/via Twitter Bob Miller is one of the most respected announcers in hockey. It probably sounded better in his head.
Hockey announcer Bob Miller on Sunday revisited an on-air gaffe he made during a game in 1981, when former Kings goalie Mario Lessard had to make do despite a broken stick — and the double entendre was no less funny now more than three decades later.
"He's standing in front of the net with about eight inches of his shaft in his hand," recounted the longtime Los Angeles broadcaster, who delivered a cringe for the ages upon his retelling.
